reviews.review: If you go in to enjoy the ride and let the predictable stuff go, it is SO FUN!!  What a movie and great ending to the saga.
Loved this movie. Was it perfect? Of course not but Abrams did a very good job of wrapping everything up after what happened in The Last Jedi.
J.J. Abrams did a great job of wrapping up the Skywalker Saga- and cleaning up the mess that TLJ created. Great action and pacing, and very reverent treatment of the characters.
Nearly incoherent in story, plot, and pacing, but a fun 2 hours romping through space, nonetheless.
There was a lot of fan service, some cheesy moments, but all in all, it's in my top 4 favorite Star Wars movies. Highly recommend seeing it. Also, the critics are dumb. Have your open opinion.

The movie was perfect, except for 2 things that bugged me. We still don't know what Finn wanted to tell Rey, and I hated the fact that we hear the same Vader breathing in the first sequence. BESIDES THAT, DISNEY SAVED THE FRANCHISE
This should get an Oscar for recovering from the last Jedi. Built for real Star Wars fans.
was a good conclusion to the series

Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker 
Spoiler Free Review: 

This last installment of the Skywalker saga had a bunch of turns that I expected, but for every predictable moment there was one just as unpredictable. This movie was in it's own way indeed a true Star Wars film. The lore of the sith was far more explored than any thing we've seen in the past. Live action anyway. J.J. Abrams kept good on his promise to introduce a few jedi that we've longed for since their introduction in both Rebels, and The Clone Wars. The movie is full of fan service, and it's core gives everything a life long fan needs to feel for the most part, complete. It's not all praises though, as the movie tends to leap past seemingly significant moments, and make it feel rushed. The return of palpatine was in fact a good call, I just wish that so much of this movie wasn't correcting the mistakes and liberties that Rian Johnson made. I had, for all intents and purposes lost hope (no pun intended) after TLJ, but this movie made me happy for the most part. J.J. Abrams said about a week ago, that force ghosts would play a major role in the conclusion and he was not wrong. I just wish he had portrayed Ahsoka Tano in a better light. 

The lightsaber fight scenes were the best of this trilogy, and the space battles were nothing short of grand. 

All in all, if you loved everything pre TLJ, you will likely love this movie. 

It is with a proud fanship, that I give Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker a 4/5 which... frankly, knowing that J.J. had to atone for previous sins of sith directors... was better than I ever anticipated this movie being.
I think alot of critics are giving this movie a bad rap but in my opinion it wraps up the Skyywalker story pretty good.
